No, I want you to prove your assertion, that the way to cure the problems you see is by killing 2 billion people. I didn't see anything in what you posted that suggested a solution would be to off a third of the planet.<br>
<br>
In fact, according to the sources you posted, that would make it worse. Seems the people you quote (except for the last one, and no, I don't believe everything I read) feel that population isn't the problem, it's pollution associated with industrialization (that'd be the talk about greenhouse gases and such).<br>
<br>
If you're slaughtering 2-4 billion people, by your own posts you're eliminating much of the undeveloped world, since it's those people that would disproportionately die from the diseases and whatnot you're unleashing (heh, yeah right, that's gonna happen naturally, sure...). Those people aren't creating the greenhouse gases and CO2 that you're quoting as causing these damaging effects. But of course that sort of genocide would leave more room for the industrialized nations to expand, and bring their polluting industry with them...<br>
<br>
Still though, we're still sidestepping the issue. Tell me, tell me, tell me, show me any source that advocates killing 2 billion people as a rational solution to solve ecological problems. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=408510">Aeani Thunderweb</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
